data.chText: 他患有头痛和食欲不振。
data.enText: He suffered from headaches and loss of appetite .
The walk gave me a good appetite.

data.chText: 不要在两餐之间吃东西，以免影响胃口。
data.enText: Don't spoil your appetite by eating between meals.

data.chText: 公众对丑事总是喜闻乐道。
data.enText: The public have an insatiable appetite for scandal.
The preview was intended to whet your appetite (= make you want more) .

simple_means.memory_skill: ap 加强 + pet 寻求；力争 + ite 表物 → 一再追求 → 欲望

example: the object of life is to satisfy as many appetencies as possible"- Granville Hick

value.def: Your appetite is your desire to eat.

example.ex: Symptoms are a slight fever, headache and loss of appetite.
example.tran: 症状包括低烧、头痛和食欲不振。

value.def: Someone's appetite for something is their strong desire for it.

example.tran: 美国人对丑闻日益增强的好奇心

example.ex: She gave him just enough information to whet his appetite.
example.tran: 她向他透露的信息刚好能吊起他的胃口。

rootsaffixes.title: pet, pit

centri 中心 + pet 寻求；力争 + al …的 → 追求中心的 → 向心的
com 共同 + pet 寻求；力争 + e → 共同追求〔一个目标〕→ 竞争
com 共同 + pet 寻求；力争 + ence 表行为 → 能力
com 共同 + pet 寻求；力争 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 →〔敢于〕竞争的 → 有能力的
com 共同 + pet 寻求；力争 + itive …的 → 有竞争力的

im 向内 + pet 寻求；力争 + uous …的 → 冲动的
in 无 + competent 有能力的 → 无能的
